byline.contributor: Ceylan Yeginsu reported from Istanbul, and Anne Barnard from Baghdad. Falih Hassan and Omar al-Jawoshy contributed reporting from Baghdad.
byline.original: By CEYLAN YEGINSU and ANNE BARNARD

abstract: Militants in Kurdistan Worker's Party carry out suicide attack on military police station in eastern Turkey, killing two soldiers and wounding 31 others; collapse of two-year cease-fire between government and militants has raised tensions in country.
lead_paragraph: About 30 others were wounded after Kurdish militants rammed a tractor loaded with explosives into a military police station in eastern Turkey, the local authorities said.

headline.main: Suicide Attack by Kurdistan Worker’s Party Members in Turkey Kills 2 Soldiers
headline.print_headline: Kurdish Militant Strike on Turkish Military Police Station Kills 2 Soldiers
